[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Understanding serialization tests**\n\nI’m thinking about a test for serialization and deserialization that can cover two uncovered areas. I wonder if I can include both tests in a dedicated file, and if it’s smooth for reporting. I need to ensure that the use of `ObjectInputStream#readObject` will work correctly without skipping. It’s also crucial to consider whether `SecureRandom` should be fixed since I’m dealing with key pair generation. I want to avoid expensive key generation while ensuring that the approach is standard and supported.\n\n**Evaluating cryptographic specs**\n\nI’m wondering if the spec values I'm looking at may not be cryptographically valid since there’s no validation process in place. That could potentially make them seem unsupported, which isn’t ideal. It’s essential to ensure that any cryptographic values I’m dealing with meet the necessary standards. I need to think through this and determine how to validate these specs effectively, so I don’t run into issues later on. It’s got me a bit concerned!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_089e5a0212af359f016a10ccbed670819fad7386cc0e3a006c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqEMzJHI2EIqkBWZffnyvdEr0Ru2lhFvoZVXZLOF9-BmafQQkuJn3qpXaNGX8ISMoQR53pj0nlmiixG4Ul2E0J288u1ai4KZ_SWnH_L-B-L5Zs2KOUNveIEyBgHWLklLnhbACaicwveFmESwZhc5p6JLwN-nX2h6n3vVU6hknEaD6Mz_tM9rqzfcdHlnBaok2ofK2jfCl8up5-Xb6hVCAlLAVnT-7MDD1zkd03Yc2KMNt1gmwHT8UMDcR8fTBbiGFyrfLnlO2VoTEU1NToen_EUXno6HgZ7MBecXEAIy6qzE1nXOKsU3__9KFF-Yarm81QEmBblmSGu-GdRJs03nZkcgbrgcl-7WE3I12A50M858DfNlLkXXVfSS8hEppcVKC230sC0l5xJTEuxFc_fMGtexvYxoRsHDVmQMfntqB6ipXUPVYR9MWXXsNbLdBDzWuqHMDz5-RtFhzrxEYYQ1Snr6pXswIT_z-gX8Esd46gRXu7KQPD6DYibfHGakzjbh3LQwIAAELSFWvWmcZ7oYKIfSZVRKZ_QgrsX0kuzZqG1X67nhaymlwlTFwJWTJjcmQAt5YaSjySyIqCppEvXMNoHGTUt-wkE1zXBocWAa0R5J5RCmk3xNoGn0AOhZ06XAkoSVLIrw9eNcMqQmjXZxPWk00wBK5Ry-E-IHxXkrjN7UT2qHvAFYc6ANudN--jjg_OxMc