ecureRandom` should be fixed since I’m dealing with key pair generation. I want to avoid expensive key generation while ensuring that the approach is standard and supported.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating cryptographic specs**\\n\\nI’m wondering if the spec values I'm looking at may not be cryptographically valid since there’s no validation process in place. That could potentially make them seem unsupported, which isn’t ideal. It’s essential to ensure that any cryptographic values I’m dealing with meet the necessary standards. I need to think through this and determine how to validate these specs effectively, so I don’t run into issues later on. It’s got me a bit concerned!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_gqRnp6obXT0PzZiyUqFP0vXv|fc_089e5a0212af359f016a10ccc936a0819fa6db384dbf30bf2b", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access -type f -maxdepth 3 -print | head -20 && find tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/build/reports/dynamic-access -type f -maxdepth 2 -print | head -20"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1333, "output": 895, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24756, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779485885599, "responseId": "resp_089e5a0212af359f016a10ccbe3c1c819f9553a6239cc2f067"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_gqRnp6obXT0PzZiyUqFP0vXv|fc_089e5a0212af359f016a10ccc936a0819fa6db384dbf30bf2b", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/bcprov-jdk15on-1.48/reflection-calls.json\ntests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/bcprov-jdk15on-1.48/resource-calls.json\ntests/src/org.bouncycastle